results.name: Decimal expansion of 1 + 22/60 + 7/60^2 + 42/60^3 + 33/60^4 + 4/60^5 + 40/60^6, Fibonacci's solution to x^3 + 2x^2 + 10x = 20.
comment: The equation has no rational solutions. Despite Fibonacci's mistake with the sixth coefficient (40 rather than 38), his solution is a remarkable achievement for the time. Plugged into the equation, it gives 20.0000000006719323...
reference: Alfred S. Posamentier & Ingmar Lehmann, The (Fabulous) Fibonacci Numbers. New York: Prometheus Books (2007): 21.
results.author: _Alonso del Arte_, Jun 28 2014
